						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar called <hi rend="italic">Mālagamba</hi> on the Siddhēśvara hill.</p>						

						<p>1589 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1511, Virōdhi, Śrāvaṇa śu. 1, Thursday, corresponding to 1589 A.D., July 3.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the setting up of two pillars for lamps by Khaṇḍērāva Timmāji of Śainīka-gotra, a subordinate of <hi rend="italic">Vajīr</hi> Haider Khan. The language of the record is Marāṭhī and the script Nāgarī.</p>						

						</summary>
